result.execSummary:
The defendant Jason Lee Schmitz was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Burglary-Motor/Trailer Home [Modifiers: PTAC, as a Party to a Crime], a class F felony, Wisconsin Statutes 943.10(1m)(e).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Defendant Jason Lee Schmitz in court with attorney Francis Xavier Rivard.  Defendant Jason Lee Schmitz in custody.  Jon D. Seifert appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Defendant appears in custody on a warrant to transport.  Warrant quashed.  Counsel informs court of joint recommendation 7 1/2 yrs. prison, 3 1/2 yrs. IC, 4 yrs. ES concurrent to all sentences currently sitting in Dunn Co.  DOB to be amended to 11/23/83.  Conditions of ES:  restitution, provide DNA sample, eval. provided by P&P and ask he be found eligible for ERP & SAP.  VR complied with, no VIS.  Court advises defendant of elements of count 1/max. penalties, felony prohibitions.  Defendant pleads guilty.  Court reviews PLQ/WOR form, advises defendant of his constitutional rights.  Defendant citizen of US and agrees facts support the charge. Court finds defendant's waiver of his constitutional rights & plea done knowingly & voluntarily, accepts plea and finds defendant guilty of count 1, Count 2 DRI.  Court sentences defendant to 7 1/2 yrs. in WI prison system, 3 1/2 yrs. IC, 4 yrs. ES concurrent with Dunn Co. Case No. 14CF277, find defendant eligible for CIP & SAP, credit for 60 days.  Conditions of ES:  Pay restitution of $800 to Dick's RV; provide DNA sample; pay costs & DNA surcharge according to a schedule set by P&P; comply with any assessment or counseling set up by P&P; advises defendant of appeal rights.  JOC to include restitution may be collected by DOC from up to 25% of prison wages.
